sub_title: Merges & Acquisitions, Integrations, Implementation, Strategic Change Management, Global Customer Care & Supply Chain PMO
summary:
With 20+ years of diverse experience in program and operations management, I was fortunate to work with clients in every industry and sector. This has expanded my outlook and knowledge as I’ve seen worked with different strategies, business models, approaches to prioritizations strategic rationales.

Global cross-functional areas covered (and not limited to), are IT, Supply & Demand, Customer Experience, Logistics & Transportations, Service & Repair, Trade Compliance, Pricing& Contracting Regulatory & Quality, Finance, Tax, VAT, Transfer Price, Legal and HR.

•	Effective portfolio prioritization and resources management tools and best practices. 
•	Proven track of 50+ successful projects in which 20+ integrations/separations, implementations, Direct/Market(s) Access, and Products launches both geographically and specifications.
•	Strong Program Management capabilities – Developed playbooks for both Project management and M&A and started a PMO Academy within Medtronic to train others on, focused on the practical HOW.
o	A strong program and change management approach, toolsets, collaboration techniques that will enable organizations to conduct projects faster and cheaper with ensured quality.
•	Break silos, collaborate effectively, and strengthen commitment and ownership senses within the organization. 
•	CEMA/EMEA deeper cultural and some linguistic knowledge for potential projects in important markets.
•	Be an integral member of the strategic advisory, linking and navigating quickly between strategy and tactical stakeholders.
•	It serves great to have people and operational sales, marketing, and account management experience, to better understand and manage stakeholders and changes. 
•	Strong knowledge of every workstream and key partners scope and expectations/interdependencies in a modern cross-functional organization (enough to manage, not to own the content).
